  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Accepted, synthetic adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. This package evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All thirteen credibility factors are listed; twelve carry structured requiredLevel and achievedLevel integers. One factor — Model Form — is documented through a qualitative expert assessment narrative in lieu of structured gradation levels, as the review team concluded that the factor's nuanced physics considerations resisted straightforward gradation assignment. The overall credibility assessment decision is Accepted based on the aggregate evidence reviewed by the assessment team.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/cou2-vad-hemolysis-req",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cou2-vad-hemolysis-claim",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-centrifugal-pump-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-generic-pump-experimental-hemolysis",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/cou2-monte-carlo-uq-results"
  ],
  "hasContextOfUse": {
    "decisionConsequence": "High",
    "description": "A CFD model is used to predict absolute hemolysis levels across operating conditions for a centrifugal blood pump used as a ventricular assist device (VAD). Model influence is HIGH (model is primary basis for hemolysis acceptance); decision consequence is HIGH (incorrect prediction could result in chronic patient hemolysis requiring clinical intervention). Model Risk Level 5 — the highest in the Morrison assessment.",
    "deviceClass": "Class III",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/cou/cou2-vad",
    "intendedUse": "Use CFD to predict absolute hemolysis index values for a Class III VAD device across 5 flow-speed combinations. Results must demonstrate hemolysis below absolute clinical threshold (not relative to predicate). Requires Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification on hemolysis predictions.",
    "modelInfluence": "High",
    "name": "COU2: Ventricular assist device use (Class III)",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
